Question 7.4.3 (Role of the Penalty Parameter in ADMM)

Function: (1/2)*x^2 + (1/2)(ax)^2
           
           = f1(x) + f2(ax)

Three iterative types:    x^{k+1} = a(cz^k-lambda^k)/(1+c*a^2)

                          z^{k+1} = (lambda^k+cax^{k+1})/(1+c)

                          lambda^{k+1} = lambda^k + c(a*x^{k+1} - z^{k+1})

a) The equation above characterizes Proposition 7.4.1 and an Alternating Directional Multiplier Method.

b) When k>=1, lambda equals z. 

     Iteration #0:
       x^{1} = a(c-1)/(1+c*a^2)

       z^{1} = (1+cax^{1})/(1+c)

       lambda^{1} = 1 + c(a*x^{1} - z^{1})

     Iteration #1:

       x^{2} = a(cz^{1}-lambda^{1})/(1+c*a^2)

             = a(c-1)z^k/(1+ca^2)

       z^{2} = (lambda^{1}+cax^{2})/(1+c)

             = (1+c^2*a^2)z^k/[(1+ca^2)(1+c)]

       lambda^{2} = lambda^{1} + c(a*x^{2} - z^{2})

                  = z^k

